TY  - JOUR
TI  - Expectations, Demand, and Observability
AU  - Polemarchakis, H. M.
AB  - [Under the assumption that demand behavior depends on intertemporal preferences as well as (point) expectations concerning future prices, it is demonstrated that under plausible conditions rationality imposes no observable restrictions on the demand function and expectations and preferences are observationally indistinguishable.]
C1  - Full publication date: May, 1983
DB  - JSTOR
